    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <p>Father Charles E. Coughlin was Roman Catholic priest, renowned as founder and pastor of the Shrine of the Little Flower in Royal Oak, Michigan. Father Coughlin gained a wide following for his Sunday afternoon radio addresses on political and economic subjects. Coughlin was a vocal opponent of Franklin Roosevelt and the New Deal.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <p>The collection consists of published sermons and Sunday evening radio addresses given by Father Coughlin in the period 1930-1940. The materials are arranged chronologically.</p>
    </scopecontent>
